---
  What was implemented

  New abstraction: CConn (in lib/chttp.h / lib/chttp.c)
  - Wraps int fd + SSL* (SSL only present when built with -DCHTTP_TLS)
  - All I/O goes through chttp_conn_write(), chttp_conn_recv(), chttp_conn_sendfile()
  - chttp_conn_close() — full TLS shutdown (used by connection owner / child after fork)
  - chttp_conn_free() — SSL_free without shutdown (used by forked parent so only child terminates TLS)

  Handler signatures changed:
  - WsHandler(int fd) → WsHandler(CConn *conn)
  - SseHandler(int fd) → SseHandler(CConn *conn)
  - req->fd → req->conn

  sendfile over TLS: automatically falls back to a read() + SSL_write() loop in chttp_conn_sendfile()

  Files changed: lib/chttp.h, lib/chttp.c, src/auth/auth.c, src/fs/fs.c, src/routes/routes.c,
  src/routes/routes.h, src/routes/static.c, src/main.c, Makefile

